modules.description: This module defines configuration options for rendering structured data as Markdown, including settings for preformatted text style, list and table formatting, tree unfolding behavior, and frame rendering. It works with grid and tree structures from the PrintBox module, allowing customization of whitespace handling, indentation width, and whether to use block or inline code formatting. Concrete use cases include adjusting output verbosity for readability versus compactness, controlling how nested data structures are displayed, and ensuring consistent formatting of code-like text.

This module renders structured document trees into Markdown, supporting customizable output through configuration options for text formatting, indentation, and structure display. It allows registration of custom extension handlers and direct conversion of PrintBox document types into Markdown strings. The configuration submodule tunes details like preformatted text style, list and table layout, and tree unfolding depth. Example uses include generating readable Markdown tables with custom indentation, rendering nested data structures with controlled verbosity, and formatting code blocks using inline or block syntax.
